message: /* Criticisms on Cinema for Peace */ new section
Consistency in award titles, fixed some links.
Irrelevant. Cinema for Peace is not an event. Disclosing COI.
Added citations on other cities. Disclosing COI.
Clarified criticism. Dieter Kosslick criticised the photo, not the Gala. Please read through the reference. Disclosing COI.
Moved criticisms to the section criticisms. Does not make sense to have it under activities. Diclosing COI.

Clarified content and added citations - Cinema for Peace is not a registered Organisation in Berlin in contrast to Cinema for Peace Foundation. Inviting editors to discuss this on talk page. disclosing COI.
Inaccurate info: Gaddafi was not a speaker. If editors wants to mention, please mention as a guest of Margarita Mathiopoulos, as shown in the referenced article para 3. disclosing COI.

removed incorrect info. Neither Cinema for Peace Initiative nor Foundation (separate entities) organsise the Cinema for Peace Gala. The Initiative and Fundation only benefit from it, just like other foundations who also benefit from it.
removed incorrect info: The source do not say what the text says.

Took our irrelevant information, the article "Most Embarrassing moments in Berlinale" do not refer to Cinema for peace as "The most embarrassing moment in Berlinale", but rather just mention it on other note.
Added actual content - refer to Talk
